A biography of this individual was written, apparently by a contemporary, which contains the following passage about St.Godric, which agrees closely with the incidents detailed in this and the following chapters. ‘⁴ Sanctum etiam Godricum, utpote confessionis et conscientiae illius medicus, saepius invisere et alloqui consuevit.
